{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The snapshotter’s delegate.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"weak"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:Qoobjc(pl)MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"id<MLNMapSnapshotterDelegate>"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"delegate"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The delegate is responsible for responding to significant changes during the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshotting process, such as the style loading. Implement a delegate to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"customize the style that is depicted by the snapshot.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You set the delegate after initializing the snapshotter but before receiving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the snapshot, typically before starting the snapshot. The snapshotter keeps a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"weak reference to its delegate, so you must keep a strong reference to it to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that your style customizations apply."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapsnapshotter\/delegate"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\